# Blog post images

All article posts use `layout: post.njk`. Image presentation is **automatic** — do not add per-post HTML, inline styles, or Tailwind classes for figures.

## How styling works

`_includes/post.njk` wraps every `.prose img` in a centered `<figure class="blog-figure">` with:

- max width ~42rem, centered in the column
- rounded border and subtle shadow
- **visible caption** from the image alt text (`<figcaption>`)

Agents only need correct Markdown in the post file; the template handles frame and label.

## Markdown syntax (required)

```markdown
![Short caption that reads as a figure label.](/images/blog/your-image.png)
```

- **Alt text = caption.** Write a full, readable label (not a filename or `image1`). It appears below the image in italic gray text.
- **Path:** `/images/blog/...` (file lives in `images/blog/` in the repo).
- **One image per line** — standard `![alt](url)` only; no raw `<img>` unless unavoidable.

## Placement

- Put images **after a paragraph**, embedded in the section flow.
- **Do not** place an image directly under a `##` or `###` heading — add at least one sentence first.
- Prefer illustrating the idea just explained, not the heading about to follow.
- Hero/lead images: after the opening hook (1–3 short paragraphs), before the first `---` or major `##` section.

## Examples (from existing posts)

```markdown
We think the same principle applies to crypto portfolio management.

![From council resolution to trade plan: the bridge translates portfolio intent into concrete on-chain legs.](/images/blog/decision-pipeline-3.png)

---

## Next section
```

```markdown
## A deliberate pause before execution

Right now, before anything touches the fund, a human reviews the execution package and decides: approve or decline.

![Human review gate: the fund manager sees the execution package, warnings, and quote expiry before signing.](/images/blog/decision-pipeline-4.png)
```

## Do not

- Hand-build `<figure>` / `<figcaption>` in Markdown unless fixing an edge case.
- Edit figure CSS in individual posts — change `_includes/post.njk` if the shared style needs updating.
- Use images in Fund / Signal updates (`layout: fund-update-post.njk`) — those pages use a different template.

## New posts

Use the `publish-blog-post` skill. When adding images, always include descriptive alt text and follow placement rules above.
